										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Have you ever taken notes during a lecture or meeting, looked at them later, and found them useless? We’ve all done it.</p>
<p>Even worse is when somebody asks to borrow your notes and quickly hands them back to you, saying, “Never mind, thanks.”</p>
<p>It’s ironic that many schools don’t give lessons on how to study or take notes effectively. These skills were addressed in an orientation class in my first year of college—which was a bit late if you ask me.</p>
<p>Our latest infographic, “The Ultimate Beginner’s Guide to Note-Taking,” makes up for what you may have missed. We give you tried-and-true tips that’ll help you take better notes and learn more.</p>
<p>See the infographic here:</p>
<p><a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/how-to-take-notes-infographic.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="https://wordcounter.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/how-to-take-notes-infographic.jpg" alt="How to Write Notes Infographic" width="900" height="3550" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3263" srcset="https://wordcounter.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/how-to-take-notes-infographic.jpg 900w, https://wordcounter.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/how-to-take-notes-infographic-152x600.jpg 152w, https://wordcounter.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/how-to-take-notes-infographic-768x3029.jpg 768w, https://wordcounter.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/how-to-take-notes-infographic-228x900.jpg 228w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></a></p>
<p>Even if you’re not a complete beginner at taking notes, I’m sure you’ll find something helpful in this list.</p>
<p>As always, we’d love it if you’d chime in with note-taking tips of your own.</p>
<p>Please comment below the infographic if you have something to share.</p>
